FBIS3-41318 "jptdd008__l94026" JPRS-TDD-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 23 February 1994 LATIN AMERICA COLOMBIA Drug Trafficker Juan David Ochoa Vasquez Awaits Sentencing Confirmation PA1502221394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 15 Feb 94 PA1502221394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] Starting today, a faceless judge has 10 days to confirm the Office of the Prosecutor General's request to sentence Juan David Ochoa Vasquez to a six and a half year prison term. [Begin recording] [Reporter Juan Ortiz] Today, the Prosecutor General's office sentenced Medellin Cartel drug trafficker Juan David Ochoa Vasquez to six and a half years in prison, within the anticipated sentencing framework for the crimes of illicit enrichment, drug trafficking, and collusion. At the hearing, which lasted approximately four hours, Deputy Prosecutor General Francisco Jose Sintura defined the terms of the negotiation, which includes the sentence handed down and the payment of a multimillion bond. [Sintura] The Prosecutor General's Office decided to impose a sentence, after granting the reductions allowed by law for confessing, voluntarily surrendering to justice, and reaching an agreement with us. [Ortiz] With this sentence, Juan David Ochoa could request parole in a little more than a year since by then he will have served 75 percent of his sentence, started on 16 February 1991. Today's agreement with Juan David Ochoa Vasquez concludes the proceedings against the Ochoa familiy, the first one to accept surrendering to the law. [end recording]
